1
00:00:01,130 --> 00:00:03,830
Hey, all you viewers out there!

2
00:00:03,830 --> 00:00:07,130
When you're watchin' Fairy Tail, make 
sure to keep the room nice and bright,

3
00:00:07,130 --> 00:00:09,240
and sit back from the screen, 'kay?

4
00:00:11,150 --> 00:00:13,650
Happy, where are you?

5
00:00:13,650 --> 00:00:14,740
Happy!

6
00:00:18,120 --> 00:00:20,480
They left me behind!

7
00:00:20,480 --> 00:00:23,280
I have to head to where Natsu 
is while I have the chance!

8
00:00:47,220 --> 00:00:51,630
It'll be all right! I'll yell it out countless times.

9
00:00:51,630 --> 00:00:56,700
I believe your every tomorrow will be shining.

10
00:00:56,700 --> 00:00:59,050
The intersection of all people

11
00:00:59,050 --> 00:01:01,660
whose dreams have come true is one point:

12
00:01:01,660 --> 00:01:06,290
Never giving up.  And that's why we're not gonna lose!

13
00:01:06,290 --> 00:01:11,470
When it seems like you'll be blown away by the headwinds,

14
00:01:11,470 --> 00:01:13,620
grasp this hand, try to take a chance.

15
00:01:13,620 --> 00:01:16,890
Because you're not alone anymore, got it?

16
00:01:20,010 --> 00:01:22,000
Go forward, more and more!

17
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:24,520
Don't give up on your awesome dream!

18
00:01:24,520 --> 00:01:25,780
That's right, don't cry!

19
00:01:25,780 --> 00:01:27,250
Move on, my way!

20
00:01:27,250 --> 00:01:29,630
Now, with the light shining down upon you.

21
00:01:29,630 --> 00:01:31,710
Don't even think about something like giving up!

22
00:01:31,710 --> 00:01:34,140
Even if you trade being hurt again for strength.

23
00:01:34,140 --> 00:01:39,630
Your eyes, always looking straight ahead,

24
00:01:39,630 --> 00:01:43,910
can surely see the light!

25
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:05,100
I'm not gonna be won over by this 
kiddy kitty merchandise, you know!

26
00:02:11,390 --> 00:02:13,730
Wait for me!

27
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:18,360
Voice of Darkness!

28
00:02:20,890 --> 00:02:26,250
We rose up for our freedom, and to save Jellal.

29
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:32,460
Don't underestimate "Mad Dog" Wally!

30
00:02:32,460 --> 00:02:35,340
We're tough thanks to all 
that "training" you gave us!

31
00:02:35,340 --> 00:02:37,380
D-Damn it!

32
00:02:47,180 --> 00:02:51,060
This guy isn't sayin' a peep! What a bore...

33
00:02:51,060 --> 00:02:56,000
You keep puttin' up a brave face, and 
you'll end up like that girl from before.

34
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,180
Hey, brat!

35
00:02:57,180 --> 00:03:02,030
Do you realize how sacred a cause 
it is to erect this R-system?

36
00:03:02,030 --> 00:03:06,740
At the moment this tower is completed, 
all of you will get to go to heaven!

37
00:03:06,740 --> 00:03:10,040
The R-system will resurrect our god!

38
00:03:10,760 --> 00:03:11,870
Shut up, pig...

39
00:03:11,870 --> 00:03:13,310
What did you say?

40
00:03:13,310 --> 00:03:14,830
Let him be.

41
00:03:14,830 --> 00:03:17,340
We're gonna have to help suppress 
the rebellion this afternoon.

42
00:03:17,910 --> 00:03:23,300
We'll continue the ceremony as many times as 
it takes until you learn to revere our god!

43
00:03:26,350 --> 00:03:27,220
God?

44
00:03:27,910 --> 00:03:29,830
I don't need anything like that.

45
00:03:30,250 --> 00:03:34,490
I don't need a god that 
can't even save one child.

46
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:39,520
Hatred...

47
00:03:41,250 --> 00:03:42,840
Hate...

48
00:03:43,410 --> 00:03:45,770
I hate everything...

49
00:03:45,770 --> 00:03:47,680
I hate them, and their god...

50
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:49,800
Everything about this world...

51
00:03:50,790 --> 00:03:55,220
Hate! And I will devour that hatred...

52
00:03:56,230 --> 00:03:59,570
People's hatred makes me grow stronger.

53
00:04:00,480 --> 00:04:01,340
Who are you?

54
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:04,250
What amusing fools.

55
00:04:04,250 --> 00:04:07,670
I'm right here among them...

56
00:04:07,670 --> 00:04:10,040
Yet they trouble themselves to resurrect me?

57
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:12,620
To give me a body?

58
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:14,730
Where are you?

59
00:04:14,730 --> 00:04:17,310
No matter how fiercely they believe,

60
00:04:17,310 --> 00:04:22,380
one cannot sense my presence 
without strong hatred.

61
00:04:23,430 --> 00:04:25,050
Jellal...

62
00:04:25,050 --> 00:04:27,390
You are quite the lucky one!

63
00:04:27,390 --> 00:04:30,370
You got to meet the god that they worship so!

64
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:36,530
My name is Zeref!

65
00:04:36,530 --> 00:04:40,970
My existence is hatred itself...

66
00:04:44,050 --> 00:04:46,750
We need to liberate Sector 8 today!

67
00:04:46,750 --> 00:04:47,780
Everyone, keep it up!

68
00:04:47,780 --> 00:04:50,480
Impossible! The guard is too tight there!

69
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:53,770
But we have to hurry and save Jellal or...

70
00:04:54,390 --> 00:04:57,740
You ain't got a prayer, Mr. Simo.

71
00:04:57,740 --> 00:05:02,020
Erza! A-Are you in love with Jellal?

72
00:05:03,060 --> 00:05:05,140
Why are you bringing that up now?

73
00:05:05,140 --> 00:05:07,050
Now is not the time to...

74
00:05:07,050 --> 00:05:09,720
I've always...

75
00:05:12,910 --> 00:05:14,740
Simon!

76
00:05:15,480 --> 00:05:16,410
That's...

77
00:05:16,410 --> 00:05:18,160
Magic Troops!

78
00:05:19,330 --> 00:05:20,520
Simon!

79
00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:22,710
Hey, wake up!

80
00:05:36,130 --> 00:05:37,110
Don't!

81
00:05:37,110 --> 00:05:38,780
Everyone, don't give up!

82
00:05:38,780 --> 00:05:40,430
You've got to fight!

83
00:05:40,430 --> 00:05:41,560
Outta the way!

84
00:05:44,630 --> 00:05:45,750
Wait...

85
00:05:45,750 --> 00:05:49,070
Save... Jellal...

86
00:05:53,050 --> 00:05:54,050
Sis!

87
00:05:54,050 --> 00:05:56,170
Erza!

88
00:06:04,150 --> 00:06:06,130
Grandpa Rob!

89
00:06:06,130 --> 00:06:10,940
My magical power may have withered, 
but I can still protect my friends!

90
00:06:11,550 --> 00:06:15,590
I will not allow such young life to perish!

91
00:06:25,780 --> 00:06:27,260
Whoa!

92
00:06:27,990 --> 00:06:29,780
He reflected the magic back!

93
00:06:32,130 --> 00:06:33,450
What's the matter?

94
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:39,440
Perhaps I have been of some use, despite 
me being such a decrepit old man...

95
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:44,540
For a wizard, one's magical power is 
the same as their life energy itself.

96
00:06:44,980 --> 00:06:50,680
And when this old man lost his magic, 
I was brought to this sorry state...

97
00:06:51,270 --> 00:06:56,910
But, Erza, your possibilities are still endless!

98
00:06:56,910 --> 00:06:58,140
Grandpa...

99
00:06:59,130 --> 00:07:01,260
It's your heart.

100
00:07:02,330 --> 00:07:03,520
Heart?

101
00:07:03,520 --> 00:07:08,070
Right. Everything begins from 
believing from your heart.

102
00:07:08,070 --> 00:07:15,140
For example, you can think of horoscopes,
faith, and prayer as forms of magic.

103
00:07:15,140 --> 00:07:20,130
They are miracles that only 
people who believe can sense.

104
00:07:20,130 --> 00:07:22,460
Only those who believe?

105
00:07:22,460 --> 00:07:24,060
That's right.

106
00:07:24,060 --> 00:07:28,620
Only those who believe in the power of 
magic, believe their your own power,

107
00:07:28,620 --> 00:07:34,840
and believe in living in harmony 
with nature are able to use magic.

108
00:07:35,420 --> 00:07:37,180
Magic, huh?

109
00:07:37,180 --> 00:07:39,300
How amazing!

110
00:07:39,810 --> 00:07:45,480
When I grow up, I want to become a witch 
and ride on a broom and fly in the sky!

111
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:47,370
I think you'll be able to.

112
00:07:47,370 --> 00:07:50,370
You'll fly free, in the wide open sky...

113
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:55,370
And I'll let you ride too, Grandpa!

114
00:07:58,690 --> 00:08:03,750
I didn't think I'd see a smile 
like that in a place like this.

115
00:08:03,750 --> 00:08:05,310
Grandpa!

116
00:08:05,310 --> 00:08:08,920
Freedom is inside of your heart.

117
00:08:09,210 --> 00:08:11,880
There is no freedom in this world.

118
00:08:12,550 --> 00:08:16,760
I am sure that your dream 
will come true, Erza...

119
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:20,730
I will grant your wish!

120
00:08:20,730 --> 00:08:22,390
Grandpa!

121
00:08:23,270 --> 00:08:26,190
No!

122
00:08:27,410 --> 00:08:30,550
Freedom is here.

123
00:08:31,900 --> 00:08:35,030
Erza, retreat! Hurry!

124
00:08:35,030 --> 00:08:36,080
Sis!

125
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:37,790
Er-chan!

126
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,060
Amazing...

127
00:09:02,060 --> 00:09:02,850
Just like that...

128
00:09:02,850 --> 00:09:04,480
Even the Magic Troops...

129
00:09:04,850 --> 00:09:06,810
Sis can use magic?

130
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:09,680
This is... magic...

131
00:09:11,390 --> 00:09:12,690
I can do this.

132
00:09:12,690 --> 00:09:16,550
With this power, I can save Jellal!

133
00:09:17,420 --> 00:09:21,160
Flying in the sky will have 
to wait for now, Grandpa.

134
00:09:22,210 --> 00:09:23,340
I...

135
00:09:24,150 --> 00:09:26,000
...will gain my freedom!

136
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:29,010
Follow me!

137
00:09:32,130 --> 00:09:33,800
Hey, what are we going to do?

138
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:34,760
Let's escape!

139
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:39,490
W-Wait!

140
00:09:39,490 --> 00:09:42,740
We were just acting under orders!

141
00:09:42,740 --> 00:09:43,770
Out of my way!

142
00:09:48,250 --> 00:09:49,430
Jellal!

143
00:09:51,940 --> 00:09:53,600
It's all right now!

144
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:55,090
It's all over!

145
00:09:55,090 --> 00:09:57,990
We fought, just like you said to, Jellal!

146
00:09:57,990 --> 00:10:03,220
Simon's seriously injured, and 
Grandpa Rob shielded me...

147
00:10:03,220 --> 00:10:06,490
There are a great number of other 
people who sacrificed their lives.

148
00:10:06,490 --> 00:10:08,200
But we won!

149
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:09,960
We've gained our freedom!

150
00:10:10,300 --> 00:10:11,320
Let's go!

151
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:13,670
Wally and the others have taken their boats.

152
00:10:13,670 --> 00:10:15,960
We can get off this island!

153
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:18,050
Erza...

154
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:21,930
There's no more running away.

155
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:25,450
True freedom is right here.

156
00:10:26,180 --> 00:10:28,230
Ooh, it's a movie lacrima!

157
00:10:28,990 --> 00:10:30,280
What's that?

158
00:10:30,280 --> 00:10:32,640
It's a lacrima that stores the data of a movie.

159
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:34,350
What's a moovee?

160
00:10:34,350 --> 00:10:35,860
A story!

161
00:10:35,860 --> 00:10:39,160
Actors act out a drama for us to watch!

162
00:10:39,160 --> 00:10:40,990
Well, it's the first time I 
ever saw one myself though...

163
00:10:45,330 --> 00:10:47,900
Too bad for you, Tony Joe.

164
00:10:47,900 --> 00:10:50,960
From the moment you met me...

165
00:10:51,250 --> 00:10:53,840
...your fate was sealed, get it?

166
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:55,140
How austere!

167
00:10:55,140 --> 00:10:56,840
He's kinda hard-edged...

168
00:10:56,840 --> 00:10:58,810
That's how a dandy should be!

169
00:10:58,810 --> 00:11:00,890
I don't get it at all.

170
00:11:01,260 --> 00:11:03,620
Sis is late...

171
00:11:04,140 --> 00:11:06,960
Jella, what are you talking about?

172
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:09,170
Let's escape from this island together!

173
00:11:09,170 --> 00:11:12,580
Erza, there is no freedom in this world.

174
00:11:13,990 --> 00:11:16,450
I realized that.

175
00:11:16,450 --> 00:11:20,910
It is not transient freedom that we require.

176
00:11:21,530 --> 00:11:23,530
It's <i>true</i> freedom.

177
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:27,680
Zeref's world!

178
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:38,210
I can understand their feelings a bit now.

179
00:11:38,210 --> 00:11:41,050
They were trying to resurrect 
this Zeref person, see.

180
00:11:41,050 --> 00:11:46,850
But these pitiful believers couldn't 
even sense Zeref's presence.

181
00:11:47,640 --> 00:11:48,560
Isn't that right?

182
00:11:49,740 --> 00:11:51,950
This tower is mine.

183
00:11:51,950 --> 00:11:53,560
I will complete it.

184
00:11:53,560 --> 00:11:55,440
I will resurrect Zeref.

185
00:11:59,790 --> 00:12:00,960
Magic?

186
00:12:01,780 --> 00:12:03,790
Save me!

187
00:12:05,060 --> 00:12:06,920
Stop it, Jellal!

188
00:12:07,270 --> 00:12:08,120
Stop?

189
00:12:09,650 --> 00:12:12,380
Don't you hate them, Erza?

190
00:12:12,380 --> 00:12:13,840
I hate them, but this is...

191
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:14,750
That's no good!

192
00:12:14,750 --> 00:12:18,360
You won't be able to sense Zeref like that!

193
00:12:18,880 --> 00:12:19,840
Stop!

194
00:12:24,170 --> 00:12:25,330
Jellal!

195
00:12:25,330 --> 00:12:26,600
What's happened?

196
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:27,930
Nothing.

197
00:12:28,210 --> 00:12:35,320
Erza, let's complete the R-system... 
I mean, the Tower of Heaven, together!

198
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:38,100
Then we can resurrect Zeref.

199
00:12:38,100 --> 00:12:39,790
Stop saying such crazy things!

200
00:12:39,790 --> 00:12:42,220
We're going to get off this island!

201
00:12:50,450 --> 00:12:55,290
Fine. If you want to go so badly, then 
you can leave this island on your own.

202
00:12:55,290 --> 00:12:56,760
On my own?

203
00:12:56,760 --> 00:12:59,370
The rest of them are all mine.

204
00:12:59,370 --> 00:13:02,760
Completing this tower will 
take a lot of work, after all.

205
00:13:02,760 --> 00:13:05,140
You don't have to worry.

206
00:13:05,140 --> 00:13:07,030
I'm not like them.

207
00:13:07,030 --> 00:13:11,700
I'll give everyone clothes, and food, and rest.

208
00:13:11,700 --> 00:13:18,450
Fear and oppression does give rise to hatred, 
but the work efficiency is far too poor.

209
00:13:18,960 --> 00:13:20,610
What are you saying?

210
00:13:20,610 --> 00:13:24,820
Everyone is already on the 
ships, waiting for us!

211
00:13:24,820 --> 00:13:28,280
No one is planning on coming 
back here and working!

212
00:13:28,280 --> 00:13:32,570
That's because they never explained 
to us the meaning behind the work.

213
00:13:32,570 --> 00:13:34,700
I will show them the meaning.

214
00:13:34,700 --> 00:13:38,170
They will work for the glory 
of the great Wizard Zeref!

215
00:13:38,170 --> 00:13:40,790
But... who would choose to 
continue sacrificing themselves?

216
00:13:40,790 --> 00:13:42,600
Sacrifice?

217
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:45,390
That's not what I need now.

218
00:13:45,390 --> 00:13:47,590
Zaref taught me, you see.

219
00:13:47,590 --> 00:13:51,470
Jellal, please, open your eyes!

220
00:13:51,470 --> 00:13:53,660
My eyes are already open.

221
00:13:54,360 --> 00:13:56,300
I have no more need for you.

222
00:13:56,300 --> 00:13:58,190
However I will allow you to live.

223
00:13:58,190 --> 00:14:01,060
Since you eliminated all those 
who stood in my way for me.

224
00:14:01,370 --> 00:14:06,050
You will leave this island and have 
your fill of that transient freedom.

225
00:14:06,050 --> 00:14:07,150
Jellal...

226
00:14:07,150 --> 00:14:10,670
But you will never speak of this to anyone.

227
00:14:10,670 --> 00:14:14,910
If the government finds out about this Tower 
of Heaven, it will be quite troublesome.

228
00:14:14,910 --> 00:14:20,580
If you try to tell someone, I will have 
to destroy this tower and everyone in it.

229
00:14:20,580 --> 00:14:23,110
You are also forbidden to come near here.

230
00:14:23,110 --> 00:14:24,880
If you set even one foot...

231
00:14:25,250 --> 00:14:26,900
Yes, I think that'll do...

232
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:29,830
First, I will make Sho disappear...

233
00:14:29,830 --> 00:14:31,780
Jellal...

234
00:14:32,470 --> 00:14:35,240
That will be your freedom!

235
00:14:35,240 --> 00:14:39,670
Live knowing that your friends' 
lives hang on your shoulders, Erza!

236
00:15:12,640 --> 00:15:18,510
I... will fight Jellal.

237
00:15:23,070 --> 00:15:30,050
We have no other option than firing 
Etherion from the Satellite Square!

238
00:15:30,050 --> 00:15:34,920
The R-system is a forbidden magic that 
must be erased from the annals of history.

239
00:15:34,920 --> 00:15:37,450
You do understand what this 
means, right everyone?

240
00:15:37,780 --> 00:15:41,220
An attack from Etherion will 
return everything to nothingness.

241
00:15:41,220 --> 00:15:43,510
Even if there are citizens there!

242
00:15:43,510 --> 00:15:48,210
And Jellal, your younger twin brother, 
will disappear as well, you know!

243
00:15:48,210 --> 00:15:50,400
Are you sure about that?

244
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:52,510
I've come to terms with that.

245
00:15:52,510 --> 00:15:56,390
All of us came this far due 
to the sacrifices of others.

246
00:15:56,690 --> 00:15:59,160
That is the Magic World of today.

247
00:15:59,160 --> 00:16:00,440
Elder Leiji!

248
00:16:00,440 --> 00:16:03,150
It will go down in history that our
country committed the crime

249
00:16:03,150 --> 00:16:07,000
of attacking the land of
Ka Elm without provocation!

250
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:10,850
That means we'll have to 
sacrifice ourselves as well.

251
00:16:10,850 --> 00:16:12,030
Elder Belno!

252
00:16:12,030 --> 00:16:14,650
The dead cannot return to life!

253
00:16:14,650 --> 00:16:19,610
When it comes time to teach the children how 
precious life is, that is what we must say!

254
00:16:19,610 --> 00:16:21,670
We must put an end to this.

255
00:16:21,670 --> 00:16:24,550
I concur with firing Etherion.

256
00:16:24,550 --> 00:16:26,190
Only one more...

257
00:16:27,850 --> 00:16:29,590
Only one more, yes?

258
00:16:29,900 --> 00:16:32,760
One more and then it is game over.

259
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:39,710
Fish...

260
00:16:39,710 --> 00:16:43,510
We played our hearts out.

261
00:16:43,510 --> 00:16:45,880
By the way... Where are we?

262
00:16:47,270 --> 00:16:49,370
Wait a second, Erza.

263
00:16:49,370 --> 00:16:52,000
That Zeref that was in your story...

264
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:54,780
Yes, you should know about Zeref too.

265
00:16:54,780 --> 00:17:00,030
I'm pretty sure they called that monster that 
came out of the Lullaby one of Zeref's demons.

266
00:17:00,360 --> 00:17:02,150
That's not all.

267
00:17:02,150 --> 00:17:06,140
I suspect that Deliora was 
also one of the Zeref's demons.

268
00:17:08,140 --> 00:17:12,250
And Jellal is trying to 
resurrect this Zeref person?

269
00:17:12,250 --> 00:17:14,590
I don't understand his motive.

270
00:17:14,590 --> 00:17:17,640
Sho... One of my friends in the past...

271
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:22,100
He said something about when the resurrection 
was complete, they'd become rulers over heaven...

272
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:27,350
But what I don't understand is why 
your past allies turned against you.

273
00:17:27,350 --> 00:17:31,800
Wasn't the traitor Jellal and not you, Erza?

274
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:36,030
He must have indoctrinated them 
somehow after I disappeared.

275
00:17:36,750 --> 00:17:40,970
But I left them here for 8 years.

276
00:17:40,970 --> 00:17:42,990
The fact is, I did betray them.

277
00:17:43,290 --> 00:17:46,200
But it was for their sake!

278
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:46,800
And yet...

279
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:48,670
Enough, Lucy.

280
00:17:50,570 --> 00:17:53,840
If I can defeat Jellal, this will all be over.

281
00:17:54,720 --> 00:17:56,840
Is that really the truth?

282
00:17:57,800 --> 00:18:04,060
Whether I win or lose this battle, 
I will vanish from this world...

283
00:18:05,280 --> 00:18:07,770
Those words are really bothering me.

284
00:18:08,910 --> 00:18:11,400
Sister... That story...

285
00:18:12,610 --> 00:18:14,270
What is that supposed to mean?

286
00:18:14,270 --> 00:18:15,610
Sho...

287
00:18:15,910 --> 00:18:19,200
You trying to get sympathy from 
your pals with that tall tale?

288
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:20,460
Give me a break!

289
00:18:20,460 --> 00:18:21,820
That's not even close to the truth!

290
00:18:23,110 --> 00:18:27,610
You blew up our ships and ran away by yourself!

291
00:18:27,610 --> 00:18:32,710
If Jellal hadn't noticed your betrayal, 
we would have all sunk into the sea!

292
00:18:32,710 --> 00:18:38,370
Jellal told us that was the fate of those who 
didn't learn the proper way to use magic!

293
00:18:38,780 --> 00:18:44,860
You were drunk from the power of magic! You 
tried to rid yourself of all of us and your past!

294
00:18:46,280 --> 00:18:49,140
Jellal told you this?

295
00:18:49,140 --> 00:18:52,560
Is that something the Erza 
you know would have done?

296
00:18:56,920 --> 00:18:58,650
What do you know?

297
00:18:58,650 --> 00:19:02,070
You don't know anything about us!

298
00:19:03,050 --> 00:19:06,460
Only Jellal's words were able to save us.

299
00:19:07,350 --> 00:19:11,290
That's why we spent these past 
8 years finishing this tower!

300
00:19:11,650 --> 00:19:12,960
For Jellal...

301
00:19:13,790 --> 00:19:16,910
If... it was all a lie...

302
00:19:18,380 --> 00:19:23,320
If you are right, Sis... And Jellal is wrong...

303
00:19:23,320 --> 00:19:24,150
That's right.

304
00:19:27,560 --> 00:19:28,460
It's you!

305
00:19:28,460 --> 00:19:30,020
Please wait, Gray-sama.

306
00:19:30,570 --> 00:19:35,310
Back then, he purposefully 
attacked your ice-clone.

307
00:19:35,310 --> 00:19:36,550
What?

308
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:40,380
There is no way a user of darkness 
techniques would not be able to notice.

309
00:19:40,780 --> 00:19:45,650
Juvia came here to ascertain 
his true intentions.

310
00:19:45,650 --> 00:19:49,600
I see Phantom's Element 4 
deserves their reputation.

311
00:19:49,600 --> 00:19:51,050
What's going on?

312
00:19:51,460 --> 00:19:56,630
Sho, I put on a performance to both trick 
you and get them to come to the tower.

313
00:19:56,630 --> 00:20:01,000
W-Why? Why would you...

314
00:20:01,890 --> 00:20:03,000
Sho...

315
00:20:03,600 --> 00:20:06,300
Everyone has been fooled by Jellal.

316
00:20:06,300 --> 00:20:09,770
I played the fool as well 
until the time was right.

317
00:20:09,770 --> 00:20:11,680
Simon, you...

318
00:20:12,680 --> 00:20:14,650
I believed in you, Erza.

319
00:20:15,590 --> 00:20:17,960
I always did for these past 8 years.

320
00:20:21,420 --> 00:20:23,520
I'm glad we could meet, Erza.

321
00:20:23,520 --> 00:20:24,810
From the bottom of my heart...

322
00:20:24,810 --> 00:20:25,900
Simon...

323
00:20:30,270 --> 00:20:31,410
How...

324
00:20:32,550 --> 00:20:35,050
How could you believe in her so much?

325
00:20:36,070 --> 00:20:37,150
Why...

326
00:20:37,880 --> 00:20:42,740
Why wasn't I able to believe in her?

327
00:20:45,500 --> 00:20:48,260
Damn!

328
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:51,640
What is the truth?

329
00:20:51,940 --> 00:20:54,980
What should I believe in?

330
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:03,900
It must be difficult to accept it all at once.

331
00:21:04,550 --> 00:21:07,780
But let me say this much...

332
00:21:08,510 --> 00:21:13,500
For these past 8 years, I have 
never forgotten about you.

333
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:17,410
I couldn't do anything for you.

334
00:21:17,900 --> 00:21:22,630
I'm sorry I was so weak...

335
00:21:22,960 --> 00:21:25,540
But now you can do it.

336
00:21:25,540 --> 00:21:26,680
Isn't that right?

337
00:21:28,300 --> 00:21:30,770
I've been waiting for this 
moment for a long time.

338
00:21:30,770 --> 00:21:33,500
Waiting for a number of powerful 
wizards to gather here.

339
00:21:33,870 --> 00:21:35,520
Powerful wizards?

340
00:21:36,610 --> 00:21:38,620
To fight Jellal.

341
00:21:38,980 --> 00:21:41,210
We'll all work together.

342
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:50,690
First, we have to prevent Wally 
and Salamander from clashing.

343
00:21:53,350 --> 00:21:55,670
What's with this room?

344
00:21:55,670 --> 00:21:57,160
It's kitty-city.

345
00:21:57,160 --> 00:22:00,210
Ooh, I like this one!

346
00:22:00,210 --> 00:22:02,520
It's a helmet!

347
00:22:03,610 --> 00:22:05,100
Let's go, Happy!

348
00:22:05,100 --> 00:22:06,850
Aye, sir!

349
00:22:07,640 --> 00:22:09,110
Or something...

350
00:22:11,500 --> 00:22:12,350
Huh?

351
00:22:15,100 --> 00:22:16,950
I... can't get it off...

352
00:22:16,950 --> 00:22:19,000
D'oh...

353
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:22,120
Well, it's funny so whatever!

354
00:22:23,670 --> 00:22:24,980
Dandy...

355
00:23:56,290 --> 00:23:58,980
Okay! I win again!

356
00:23:58,980 --> 00:24:00,550
That's 9 wins in a row.

357
00:24:00,550 --> 00:24:01,490
Play me again!

358
00:24:01,490 --> 00:24:03,910
This time I'm going to win, for sure!

359
00:24:03,910 --> 00:24:06,600
Natsu, you say that every time.

360
00:24:06,600 --> 00:24:08,710
I'm tired already.

361
00:24:08,710 --> 00:24:10,860
Then I win by default, right?

362
00:24:10,860 --> 00:24:13,380
All right! I win!

363
00:24:13,730 --> 00:24:16,140
Next time: Heaven's Game

364
00:24:16,390 --> 00:24:19,510
It's against the rules to 
change the rules unilaterally!

365
00:24:19,510 --> 00:24:21,720
Freeedddooom!

366
00:24:22,230 --> 00:24:24,480
Uh, I think he broke.

